  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Monocentric comparative group study comparing the efficacy and short-term tolerance of a
      propulsion type oral appliance (Herbst) with a retention type device (ORM) used in the
      treatment of sleep apnea syndrome. The investigators hypothesized both appliances would be
      equally effective and tolerated.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
